quran[49]{c,v,t}:
  15,1,Those are the signs of the Book and of a perspicuous Qur'an
  15,2,Many a time will those who disbelieve fain they had been resigned
  15,3,"Leave them to eat and enjoy themselves and let hope beguile them, but they at length shall know"
  15,4,We never destroyed a city without it had its noted doom
  15,5,"No nation can hasten on its appointed time, nor put it off"
  15,6,"But they say, 'O thou to whom the Reminder has been sent down! verily, thou art possessed"
  15,7,Why dost thou not bring us the angels if thou dost tell the truth
  15,8,We sent not down the angels save by right nor even then would these be respited
  15,9,"Verily, we have sent down the Reminder, and, verily, we will guard it"
  15,10,And we sent before thee among the sects of those of yore
  15,11,But there never came an apostle to them but they mocked at him
  15,12,Such conduct also will we put into the hearts of the sinners
  15,13,"They will not believe therein, but the course of those of yore is run"
  15,14,But had we opened to them a door of the sky and they had mounted up into it all the while
  15,15,"then also had they said, 'Our eye-sight is only intoxicated; nay, we are an enchanted people"
  15,16,"And we have placed in the sky the signs of the zodiac, and have made them seemly to the beholders"
  15,17,and we have guarded them from every pelted devil
  15,18,"save from such as steal a hearing, and there follows him an obvious shooting-star"
  15,19,"And the earth we have stretched out and have thrown on it firm mountains, and have caused to grow upon it of everything a measured quantity"
  15,20,"And we have made for you means of livelihood therein, and for those for whom ye have not to provide"
  15,21,"Nor is there aught but the treasuries of it are with us, and we do not send it down save in a noted quantity"
  15,22,"And we send forth the impregnating winds, and we send down water from the sky, and we give it to you to drink, nor is it ye who store it up"
  15,23,"And we, verily, we quicken and kill; and we are of (all things) heirs"
  15,24,"And we already know the foremost of you, and we know the laggards too"
  15,25,"And, verily, it is your Lord who will gather you; verily, He is wise and knowing"
  15,26,And we did create man from crackling clay of black mull wrought in form
  15,27,And the ginns had we created before of smokeless fire
  15,28,"And when thy Lord said to the angels, 'Verily, I am creating a mortal from crackling clay of black mud wrought into shape"
  15,29,"And when I have fashioned it, and breathed into it of my spirit, then fall ye down before it adoring"
  15,30,And the angels adored all of them together
  15,31,"save Iblis, who refused to be among those who adored"
  15,32,"He said, 'O Iblis! what ails thee that thou art not among those who adore"
  15,33,"Said he, 'I would not adore a mortal whom Thou hast created from crackling clay of black mud wrought into form"
  15,34,"He said, 'Then get thee forth therefrom, and, verily, thou art to be pelted"
  15,35,"And, verily, the curse is upon thee until the day of judgment"
  15,36,"Said he, 'O my Lord! respite me until the day when they shall be raised"
  15,37,"He said, 'Then, verily, thou art of the respited"
  15,38,until the day of the noted time
  15,39,"He said, 'O my Lord! for that Thou hast seduced me I will surely make it seem seemly for them on earth, and I will surely seduce them all together"
  15,40,save such of Thy servants amongst them as are sincere
  15,41,"Said He, 'This is a right way against me"
  15,42,"Verily, my servants thou hast no authority over, save over those who follow thee of such as are seduced"
  15,43,"and, verily, hell is promised to them all together"
  15,44,It has seven doors; at every door is there a separate party of them
  15,45,"Verily, those who fear God shall dwell amidst gardens and springs"
  15,46,Enter ye therein with peace in safety
  15,47,And we will strip off whatever ill-feeling is in their breasts; as brethren on couches face to face
  15,48,"No toil shall touch them therein, nor shall they be brought forth therefrom"
  15,49,"Inform my servants that I am the pardoning, the merciful"